Variable Description: Unique identifier for each claim
Hashed identifier for each veteran
Age of the veteran at the time of claim
Gender of the veteran ('M' = Male, 'F' = Female, 'O' = Other/Nonbinary)
Military branch in which the veteran served
Type of benefit or compensation claim
ICD-10 diagnosis code related to the claim
Monetary amount requested in the claim
Date the claim was filed
Date the claim was adjudicated
Final decision on the claim [(Denied' 'Approved' 'Partial Approval')
Code for the VA facility processing the claim
Type of healthcare provider ('Internal VA',  'Community Care'
State of the veteran or processing facility
Percent disability rating assigned
Indicator if claim involves PTSD (1 = Yes, 0 = No)
Number of times the claim has been appealed
Veteran's residence classification
Days between filing and decision
Whether condition is connected to service (1 = Yes, 0 = No)
